{
  "texts": [
    "Then, the REFLEC-TOOL can take the action with the help of similar successful trajectories as below:",
    "The agent then solves the task with tool-wise reflection, where the verifier evaluates the agent's action in each step according to the action-wise experience.",
    "Inspired by Snell et al. (2024), we adopt two types of verification methods, iterative refinement and candidate selection, to fully explore the effectiveness of tool-wise experience in the toolwise reflection process.",
    "in §5.2, we find that each variant has its own advantages: Iterative Refinement performs better when the model's capabilities are limited, while Candidate Selection is more effective when the model is stronger, thereby maximizing the model's potential.",
    "Iterative Refinement In the sequence refinement method, the verifier will keep refining the agent action until it achieves the max refine step."
  ]
}